f  locations around the world operating solely for private banking business turkeyedit hsbc bank as is now the fifth largest private bank in turkey having expanded through internal financing and via acquisition since entering the market in  the bank has a network of around  branches offering products and services to corporate commercial and personal customers both under the hsbc brand as well as the advantage brand controversyedit withdrawal of graduate overdraftsedit in july  hsbc suddenly withdrew its interestfree overdrafts for graduates students graduating that year discovered that they were to face unexpected bills of up to £ a year students mobilised protests using the social networking website facebook and in august hsbc reversed their policy freezing overdraft charges to recent graduates and pledging to repay charges deducted in august while holding talks with the national union of students data lossedit in april  hsbc confirmed the loss of unencrypted data disks containing life insurance policy details for  customers in february  hsbc sent a letter dated february  to an unknown number of recipients stating that they were writing to inform you of the potential compromise of some of your former account information with us the date and extent of the loss were not given however hsbc offered a years enrollment to itac sentinel and advised vigilance for  to  months as well as recommending contacting the three major credit bureaus to place a fraud alert on the credit profile cultural insensitivityedit in  hsbc were accused of cultural insensitivity in an advertising campaign featuring an overweight white man dressed to look like a sumo wrestler the campaign upset members of britains japanese community who claimed the mans skin tone was darkened and makeup was applied to narrow his eyes hsbc denied making the model appear to be from a specific country or region but admitted makeup was applied and skin tone was tanned links to the arms tradeedit in december  the british antipoverty charity war on want released a report documenting the extent to which hsbc and other uk commercial banks invest in provide banking services for and make loans to arms companies the charity writes in its report that hsbc holds shares in the global arms industry totalling £ million and serves as principal banker for meggitt one of the uks largest arms companies the report also details hsbcs dealings with known producers of cluster munitions and depleted uranium munitions closing muslim clients organisations and mosques accountsedit in  hsbc closed north london central mosques account and some muslim clients and groups accounts several sources report that hsbc closed them because they donated their money to palestine during the recent conflict see alsoedit companies portal hsbc bank international midland bank plc referencesedit  running to hsbc makes shares european bank winner bloombergcom  october    hiscott graham  july  number of bank branches at lowest level for over  years daily mirror retrieved  november    hsbc headquarters to relocate from london to birmingham bbc news  march  retrieved  march    garside juliette  march  hsbc to base ringfenced retail banking operation in birmingham the guardian retrieved  november    wolfe hazel  september  the brand midland bank won’t return as hsbc will be called hsbc uk economic news daily retrieved  november    goodley simon  november  clara furse to chair hsbcs retail arm the guardian retrieved  november    first response survey december  research undertaken agency among  current account holders across the uk between  november  and  december   hsbc algeria hsbc algeria retrieved    hsbc ireland sbpostie dead link  collinson patrick levene tony  august  now its facebook vs hsbc the guardian london   macleod donald  august  students celebrate facebook triumph over hsbc the guardian london   bowers simon  april  hsbc loses disk with policy details of  customers the guardian london   day elizabeth  august  bank loses face over brian the sumo fake guardiancouk london   salter jessica  august  hsbc embroiled in sliteye row over advert telegraphcouk london   banking on bloodshed waronwantorg   hsbc closes some muslim groups accounts bbc news  july    robinson wills  july  hsbc bank accused of islamaphobia after telling muslim groups it will close down accounts  daily mail online mail online london   haroon siddique hsbc shuts accounts of muslim organisations including finsbury park mosque the guardian   hsbc closes three muslim organisations accounts bbc news   hsbc angers muslim leaders by closing account of finsbury park mosque the evening standard   tadeo maria  july  hsbc closes bank accounts belonging to muslim clients in the uk the independent london   barrett david  july  muslim bank accounts closed by hsbc in wake of money laundering fine telegraphcouk london   hsbc terminates gazalinked islamic charity’s bank account and others rtcom   giles fraser hsbc the bank that likes to say no to muslim accounts the guardian   gmbwatch uk muslim brotherhood leader says hsbc closes his bank accounts claims closures part of action against palestinian activists the global muslim brotherhood daily watch  external linksedit first direct hsbc bank armenia hsbc bank uk hsbc france hsbc poland hsbc group hsbc private bank hsbc bank international v t e hsbc board of directors douglas flint group chairman stuart gulliver group ceo iain mackay group finance director marc moses group chief risk officer phillip ameen kathleen l casey safra a catz laura cha lord evans of weardale joachim faber rona fairhead sam laidlaw john lipsky rachel lomax heidi miller sir simon robertson jonathan symonds brands first direct hang seng bank hsbc hsbc expat hsbc premier hsbc private bank hsbc trinkaus ms money proa sabb principal local banks argentina australia canada peoples republic of china egypt france germany hong kong india malaysia middle east mexico panama poland saudi arabia sri lanka taiwan t